  "text": "Concerning oral exposure during critical periods of life like in newborns, a very recent study suggests that infants can be exposed to silver and gold nanoparticles via breastmilk [CITATION_1] . Silver nanoparticles administered intravenously or orally to lactating mice resulted in silver nanoparticle detection in breastmilk, and subsequently silver nanoparticles were found to accumulate in the brains of offspring. During the earliest months of life, the young mice did not show any neurologic abnormalities. However, the consequences of nanoparticle exposure on brain function may appear on a longer time scale and thus this should be evaluated.",
